y sentence\n- Could be grouped with OCR corruption or as separate pattern\n\n**Pattern 5: Title preceded by metadata line**\n- Ogórkowa Zupa: metadata `Lato | Zupy | DLA 4 OSÓB` appears before the title, and title is ALL CAPS. Extracted nothing.\n\n**Pattern 6: Title not at top of document**\n- Mushroom Risotto: The document starts with body text mid-recipe, a different recipe title appears later. Extractor picked up that wrong title.\n\nNow I'm organizing these patterns into cleaner groups. Digit-for-letter OCR corruption shows two distinct behaviors: some titles get rejected entirely and return nothing, like Braised Cod with White Wine and Roasted Beet and Walnut Dip, while others like Drożdże Sernik get rejected but still extract a sentence from the body instead.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":11611,"cache_read_input_tokens":10352,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":11611},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3d995162-a677-4d2f-a075-9536e5856117","uuid":"5bbdcdc0-1b46-4aa7-a85e-37b9c530c0f9"}
